    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-06-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <head>113. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to Director of Central
                    Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d113fn1">Source: National Security Council,
                        Carter Administration Intelligence Files S–Z, Box 27, Zaire. No
                        classification marking;</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-06-19">June 19, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Responses to your Memorandum of June 16 regarding the Reinforcement of our
                        Collection Capabilities [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                            declassified</hi>]; and to your Memorandum of June 19 regarding
                        provision of Intelligence Support to the [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line
                            not declassified</hi>]</item>
                </list>
                <p>I have reviewed your memorandum of June 16,<note n="2" xml:id="d113fn2">Attached
                        but not printed.</note> and I support and approve your initiative to
                    reinforce our intelligence capabilities [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                        declassified</hi>], as outlined in your memorandum.</p>
                <p>I have reviewed your memorandum of June 19 regarding provision of intelligence
                    support to [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>], and I
                    approve the provision of intelligence and other support, as outlined in your
                    memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d113fn3">Printed from an unsigned copy.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <note rend="inline">
                        <hi rend="strong">Attachment</hi>
                    </note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="strong">Memorandum From Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                                corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName> to the President’s Assistant for
                            National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BZK_1"
                                >Brzezinski</persName>)</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1978-06-19">June 19, 1978</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>[Source: National Security Council, Carter Administration Intelligence Files
                        S–Z, Box 27, [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>].
                        Secret. 2 pages not declassified.]</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
